14#include <config.h>
15
16#include <stdbool.h>
17
18#include <isc/mem.h>
19#include <isc/rwlock.h>
20#include <isc/util.h>
21
22#include <dns/dbtable.h>
23#include <dns/db.h>
24#include <dns/rbt.h>
25#include <dns/result.h>
26
27struct dns_dbtable {
28 /* Unlocked. */
29 unsigned int magic;
30 isc_mem_t * mctx;
31 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
32 isc_mutex_t lock;
33 isc_rwlock_t tree_lock;
34 /* Locked by lock. */
35 unsigned int references;
36 /* Locked by tree_lock. */
37 dns_rbt_t * rbt;
38 dns_db_t * default_db;
39};
40
41#define DBTABLE_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D', 'B', '-', '-')
42#define VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(dbtable, DBTABLE_MAGIC)
43
44static void
45dbdetach(void *data, void *arg) {
46 dns_db_t *db = data;
47
48 UNUSED(arg);
49
50 dns_db_detach(&db);
51}
52
53isc_result_t
54dns_dbtable_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
55 dns_dbtable_t **dbtablep)
56{
57 dns_dbtable_t *dbtable;
58 isc_result_t result;
59
60 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
61 REQUIRE(dbtablep != NULL && *dbtablep == NULL);
62
63 dbtable = (dns_dbtable_t *)isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*dbtable));
64 if (dbtable == NULL)
65 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
66
67 dbtable->rbt = NULL;
68 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, dbdetach, NULL, &dbtable->rbt);
69 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
70 goto clean1;
71
72 isc_mutex_init(&dbtable->lock);
73
74 result = isc_rwlock_init(&dbtable->tree_lock, 0, 0);
75 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
76 goto clean3;
77
78 dbtable->default_db = NULL;
79 dbtable->mctx = NULL;
80 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &dbtable->mctx);
81 dbtable->rdclass = rdclass;
82 dbtable->magic = DBTABLE_MAGIC;
83 dbtable->references = 1;
84
85 *dbtablep = dbtable;
86
87 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
88
89 clean3:
90 isc_mutex_destroy(&dbtable->lock);
91
92 dns_rbt_destroy(&dbtable->rbt);
93
94 clean1:
95 isc_mem_putanddetach(&mctx, dbtable, sizeof(*dbtable));
96
97 return (result);
98}
99
100static inline void
101dbtable_free(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable) {
102 /*
103 * Caller must ensure that it is safe to call.
104 */
105
106 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
107
108 if (dbtable->default_db != NULL)
109 dns_db_detach(&dbtable->default_db);
110
111 dns_rbt_destroy(&dbtable->rbt);
112
113 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
114
115 isc_rwlock_destroy(&dbtable->tree_lock);
116
117 dbtable->magic = 0;
118
119 isc_mem_putanddetach(&dbtable->mctx, dbtable, sizeof(*dbtable));
120}
121
122void
123dns_dbtable_attach(dns_dbtable_t *source, dns_dbtable_t **targetp) {
124 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(source));
125 REQUIRE(targetp != NULL && *targetp == NULL);
126
127 LOCK(&source->lock);
128
129 INSIST(source->references > 0);
130 source->references++;
131 INSIST(source->references != 0);
132
133 UNLOCK(&source->lock);
134
135 *targetp = source;
136}
137
138void
139dns_dbtable_detach(dns_dbtable_t **dbtablep) {
140 dns_dbtable_t *dbtable;
141 bool free_dbtable = false;
142
143 REQUIRE(dbtablep != NULL);
144 dbtable = *dbtablep;
145 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
146
147 LOCK(&dbtable->lock);
148
149 INSIST(dbtable->references > 0);
150 dbtable->references--;
151 if (dbtable->references == 0)
152 free_dbtable = true;
153
154 UNLOCK(&dbtable->lock);
155
156 if (free_dbtable)
157 dbtable_free(dbtable);
158
159 *dbtablep = NULL;
160}
161
162isc_result_t
163dns_dbtable_add(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db) {
164 isc_result_t result;
165 dns_db_t *dbclone;
166
167 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
168 REQUIRE(dns_db_class(db) == dbtable->rdclass);
169
170 dbclone = NULL;
171 dns_db_attach(db, &dbclone);
172
173 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
174 result = dns_rbt_addname(dbtable->rbt, dns_db_origin(dbclone), dbclone);
175 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
176
177 return (result);
178}
179
180void
181dns_dbtable_remove(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db) {
182 dns_db_t *stored_data = NULL;
183 isc_result_t result;
184 dns_name_t *name;
185
186 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
187
188 name = dns_db_origin(db);
189
190 /*
191 * There is a requirement that the association of name with db
192 * be verified. With the current rbt.c this is expensive to do,
193 * because effectively two find operations are being done, but
194 * deletion is relatively infrequent.
195 * XXXDCL ... this could be cheaper now with dns_rbt_deletenode.
196 */
197
198 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
199
200 result = dns_rbt_findname(dbtable->rbt, name, 0, NULL,
201 (void **) (void *)&stored_data);
202
203 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
204 INSIST(stored_data == db);
205
206 (void)dns_rbt_deletename(dbtable->rbt, name, false);
207 }
208
209 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
210}
211
212void
213dns_dbtable_adddefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db) {
214 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
215 REQUIRE(dbtable->default_db == NULL);
216 REQUIRE(dns_name_compare(dns_db_origin(db), dns_rootname) == 0);
217
218 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
219
220 dbtable->default_db = NULL;
221 dns_db_attach(db, &dbtable->default_db);
222
223 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
224}
225
226void
227dns_dbtable_getdefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t **dbp) {
228 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
229 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && *dbp == NULL);
230
231 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
232
233 dns_db_attach(dbtable->default_db, dbp);
234
235 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
236}
237
238void
239dns_dbtable_removedefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable) {
240 REQUIRE(VALID_DBTABLE(dbtable));
241
242 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
243
244 dns_db_detach(&dbtable->default_db);
245
246 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
247}
248
249isc_result_t
250dns_dbtable_find(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, const dns_name_t *name,
251 unsigned int options, dns_db_t **dbp)
252{
253 dns_db_t *stored_data = NULL;
254 isc_result_t result;
255 unsigned int rbtoptions = 0;
256
257 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && *dbp == NULL);
258
259 if ((options & DNS_DBTABLEFIND_NOEXACT) != 0)
260 rbtoptions |= DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT;
261
262 RWLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
263
264 result = dns_rbt_findname(dbtable->rbt, name, rbtoptions, NULL,
265 (void **) (void *)&stored_data);
266
267 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH)
268 dns_db_attach(stored_data, dbp);
269 else if (dbtable->default_db != NULL) {
270 dns_db_attach(dbtable->default_db, dbp);
271 result = DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH;
272 } else
273 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
274
275 RWUNLOCK(&dbtable->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
276
277 return (result);
278}
